The paper deals with a graph problem involving threshold values for vertices, which suggests it could belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. Additionally, the use of clique-width as a parameter suggests a possible connection to Graph Theory (cs.GT). The problem of selecting a smallest possible initial set of vertices also has applications in Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
